wiki_catalogs.name: Project Overview
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive content for the PrismStyle AI project overview section. Explain the AI-powered fashion companion's purpose, core functionality, and target audience. Document the key features including smart wardrobe management, clothing recognition, and outfit generation capabilities. Describe the cross-platform Flutter architecture supporting iOS 18+ and Android platforms. Include the technology stack overview, design philosophy focusing on privacy-first and offline-first principles. Provide high-level system architecture diagram showing the relationship between Flutter application, native iOS Swift integration, Android Kotlin implementation, and Supabase backend. Address the project's positioning in the fashion tech space and its unique value propositions for users seeking intelligent wardrobe management solutions.

wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive documentation for PrismStyle AI's iOS platform integration. Address App Store submission requirements and iOS platform-specific limitations.

wiki_overview.content:
<blog>

# PrismStyle AI - Fashion & Style Assistant

## Project Introduction

PrismStyle AI is an innovative AI-powered fashion companion designed for iOS 18+ and Android platforms. This cross-platform application serves as a comprehensive digital wardrobe assistant that combines cutting-edge machine learning with intuitive user experience to revolutionize personal styling.

### Purpose Statement
The application addresses the growing need for intelligent fashion management by providing users with automated clothing recognition, personalized outfit generation, and smart wardrobe organization capabilities powered entirely by on-device AI processing.

### Core Goals and Objectives
- **Zero-cost AI Classification**: Leverage ensemble AI combining TFLite, Apple Vision Framework, and Core ML for free, high-accuracy clothing recognition
- **Privacy-First Approach**: Ensure 100% offline capability with no user tracking or data collection
- **Cross-Platform Compatibility**: Deliver seamless experience across iOS and Android devices
- **Real-Time Integration**: Provide weather-based outfit recommendations and social validation features

### Target Audience
- Fashion-conscious individuals seeking smart wardrobe management
- Mobile developers interested in AI integration patterns
- Privacy-focused users preferring local processing over cloud-based solutions
- Cross-platform Flutter developers exploring advanced AI implementations

## Technical Architecture

The PrismStyle AI application follows a modern Flutter architecture with clear separation of concerns and robust service layer design.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Main Application Entry] --> B[UI Presentation Layer]
    A --> C[Service Layer]
    A --> D[Core Configuration]
    
    B --> B1[Home Dashboard]
    B --> B2[Camera Capture]
    B --> B3[Outfit Generator]
    B --> B4[Wardrobe Management]
    B --> B5[User Profile]
    
    C --> C1[AI Services]
    C --> C2[Backend Services]
    C --> C3[Utility Services]
    
    C1 --> C11[Clothing Classifier]
    C1 --> C12[Color Detection]
    C1 --> C13[Ensemble AI Engine]
    
    C2 --> C21[Supabase Service]
    C2 --> C22[Weather Service]
    C2 --> C23[OpenAI Service]
    
    D --> D1[Routing System]
    D --> D2[Theme Management]
    D --> D3[Dependency Injection]
```

### Component Breakdown

**Presentation Layer**: Modular UI components organized by feature domains including camera capture, outfit generation, wardrobe management, and user profile sections.

**Service Layer**: Comprehensive business logic encapsulated in specialized services for AI processing, backend communication, and utility functions.

**Core Configuration**: Centralized routing, theming, and dependency management ensuring consistent application behavior across all platforms.

### Design Patterns

The application implements several key design patterns:
- **Singleton Pattern**: Used extensively for service classes like SupabaseService and EnsembleAIService
- **Factory Pattern**: For creating different types of UI widgets and services
- **Observer Pattern**: Through Flutter's reactive state management and Supabase real-time subscriptions
- **Strategy Pattern**: For interchangeable AI model implementations

## Key Implementation

### Main Entry Points

The application bootstraps through a carefully orchestrated initialization sequence that ensures optimal performance and user experience.

**Application Entry Point** (`lib/main.dart`)
- Initializes Supabase for authentication and real-time database functionality
- Sets up local notification service for user engagement
- Configures AI clothing classifier with platform-specific optimizations
- Implements comprehensive error handling with custom error widget
- Locks device orientation to portrait mode for consistent UX

**Core Export Module** (`lib/core/app_export.dart`)
- Provides centralized imports for commonly used packages and utilities
- Maintains consistent export patterns across the application
- Enables easy dependency management and modular architecture

### Core Modules

**Routing System** (`lib/routes/app_routes.dart`)
- Defines all application routes with clear naming conventions
- Implements route-based navigation with parameter passing
- Supports both programmatic and declarative navigation patterns

**Theming System** (`lib/theme/app_theme.dart`)
- Implements comprehensive light and dark theme support
- Defines custom color palettes optimized for fashion applications
- Provides typography systems with Google Fonts integration
- Ensures accessibility compliance with proper contrast ratios

### Configuration Approach

**Dependency Management** (`pubspec.yaml`)
- Modern Flutter dependency specification with version pinning
- Strategic inclusion of AI libraries (tflite_flutter, image)
- Integration of privacy-focused packages (supabase_flutter)
- Responsive design support through sizer package

**Environment Configuration** (`env.json`)
- Centralized environment variable management
- Secure credential storage for Supabase integration
- Flexible configuration for development and production environments

### External Dependencies

The project leverages a carefully curated set of dependencies:

**Core Framework Dependencies**:
- `supabase_flutter`: Backend-as-a-Service with real-time capabilities
- `tflite_flutter`: On-device machine learning inference
- `google_fonts`: Typography optimization with Google Fonts
- `provider`: State management with reactive patterns

**Feature-Specific Dependencies**:
- `camera`: Native camera integration for iOS and Android
- `image_picker`: Gallery access and image selection
- `permission_handler`: Platform-specific permission management
- `geolocator/geocoding`: Location services for weather integration

### Integration Points

**Apple Vision Framework Integration** (`ios/Runner/AppleVisionHandler.swift`)
- Native Swift implementation for iOS-specific AI capabilities
- Vision framework integration for free, high-accuracy image classification
- Seamless bridging between Flutter and native iOS components

**Supabase Real-time Database** (`lib/services/supabase_service.dart`)
- Real-time synchronization of user data across devices
- Automatic conflict resolution and offline-first architecture
- Comprehensive CRUD operations with typed data models

**Weather Integration** (`lib/services/weather_service.dart`)
- Open-Meteo API integration for accurate weather data
- Location-based recommendations with fallback mechanisms
- Comprehensive error handling for network failures

### Component Relationship Diagrams

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[CameraCapture] --> B[ClothingClassifierService]
    A --> C[ColorDetectionService]
    B --> D[EnsembleAIService]
    C --> D
    D --> E[AI Classification Results]
    E --> F[Outfit Generator]
    F --> G[Supabase Service]
    G --> H[Real-time Updates]
```

## Key Features

### Functionality Overview

**Smart Camera Capture** (`lib/presentation/camera_capture/camera_capture.dart`)
- Advanced AI-powered clothing recognition with ensemble model approach
- Real-time image processing with confidence scoring
- Multi-source image capture (camera and gallery)
- Comprehensive error handling and user guidance

**Digital Wardrobe Management** (`lib/presentation/wardrobe_management/wardrobe_management.dart`)
- Structured organization of clothing items with categorization
- Visual filtering and search capabilities
- Integration with AI-generated attributes for enhanced discovery
- Social sharing and community validation features

**Outfit Generation Engine** (`lib/presentation/outfit_generator/outfit_generator.dart`)
- Intelligent combination creation based on compatibility algorithms
- Weather-aware recommendations with real-time data integration
- AI-powered suggestions through OpenAI integration
- Personalized style analytics and preference tracking

**Ensemble AI Classification** (`lib/services/ensemble_ai_service.dart`)
- Multi-model approach combining TFLite, Apple Vision, and Core ML
- Weighted voting system for optimal accuracy
- Fallback heuristics ensuring reliable performance
- Platform-specific optimizations for iOS and Android

### Implementation Highlights

**AI Model Architecture** (`lib/services/ensemble_ai_service.dart`)
- Custom trained DeepFashion2 model with 13+ clothing categories
- Apple Vision Framework integration for iOS native classification
- Core ML optimization for hardware-accelerated inference
- Comprehensive error handling and model fallback strategies

**Real-time Data Synchronization** (`lib/services/supabase_service.dart`)
- Supabase real-time subscriptions for instant data updates
- Conflict-free replicated data types for offline-first architecture
- Type-safe data models with comprehensive validation
- Stream-based architecture for reactive UI updates

**Privacy-Focused Design** (`lib/main.dart`)
- 100% offline capability with optional cloud sync
- No user tracking or data collection
- Encrypted local storage for sensitive information
- Transparent permission requests with clear explanations

### Feature Architecture Diagrams

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> CameraInitialization
    CameraInitialization --> ImageCapture: User Action
    ImageCapture --> AIProcessing: Image Bytes
    AIProcessing --> ClassificationComplete: Model Results
    ClassificationComplete --> OutfitGeneration: Valid Attributes
    ClassificationComplete --> ErrorHandling: Invalid Input
    OutfitGeneration --> RecommendationDisplay: Suggestions
    RecommendationDisplay --> UserInteraction: Feedback
    UserInteraction --> OutfitGeneration: Adjust Parameters
    ErrorHandling --> CameraInitialization: Retry
    RecommendationDisplay --> [*]: Save/Share
```

The PrismStyle AI application represents a sophisticated blend of modern Flutter development practices, advanced machine learning integration, and privacy-focused design principles. Its modular architecture ensures maintainability and scalability while delivering exceptional user experience across multiple platforms.

---

**Sources:**
- [pubspec.yaml](pubspec.yaml)
- [main.dart](lib/main.dart)
- [app_export.dart](lib/core/app_export.dart)
- [app_routes.dart](lib/routes/app_routes.dart)
- [app_theme.dart](lib/theme/app_theme.dart)
- [supabase_service.dart](lib/services/supabase_service.dart)
- [ensemble_ai_service.dart](lib/services/ensemble_ai_service.dart)
- [home_dashboard.dart](lib/presentation/home_dashboard/home_dashboard.dart)
- [outfit_generator.dart](lib/presentation/outfit_generator/outfit_generator.dart)
- [camera_capture.dart](lib/presentation/camera_capture/camera_capture.dart)
- [openai_service.dart](lib/services/openai_service.dart)
- [weather_service.dart](lib/services/weather_service.dart)
- [README.md](README.md)
- [AppleVisionHandler.swift](ios/Runner/AppleVisionHandler.swift)

</blog>
